   have been developed for the task, including a recent proliferation of
   deep-learning based approaches. A variety of datasets have also been
   developed, exemplifying various manifestations of the hate-speech
   detection problem. We present here a large-scale empirical comparison of
   deep and shallow hate-speech detection methods, mediated through the
   three most commonly used datasets. Our goal is to illuminate progress in
