   performance across languages by 0.5-9\%. We also observe substantial F1
   gains of 1-8\% by reformulating hate speech detection as
   Entailment-style problem. We further probe the contextual models and
   observe that higher layers encode implicit hate while lower layers focus
   on explicit hate, highlighting the importance of token-level
   understanding for explicit and context-level for implicit hate speech
